<!-- CycloneDDS configuration for Go2 EDU + same-host ROS 2 nav stack on this Jetson.

     TWO interfaces: onboard eno1 (PRIMARY, Go2-facing) + lo (same-host loopback).

     WHY lo is required here (empirical, 2026-06-16, verified in-container):
       This Jetson's physical NIC does NOT loop multicast back to other local
       participants (self-loopback broken — see memory go2-dds-multicast-blocker).
       So a single-physical-interface bind (eno1 only) makes SAME-HOST DDS discovery
       fail: a demo pub/echo on cyclonedds heard 0/12 msgs with eno1-only, 12/12 once
       `lo` was added. Same-host discovery is mandatory — the whole nav stack (nav2
       <-> costmaps <-> rko_lio <-> icp <-> go2_sport_bridge) and the operator's
       `ros2 service call .../enable` all rely on it. eno1-only silently breaks them.

     WHY eno1 is PRIMARY (priority 10 > lo's 1):
       The external Go2 must reach us on our 192.168.123.x locator, so the onboard
       NIC's address is advertised as the preferred unicast locator. eno1 also
       delivers the Go2's INBOUND multicast (the USB-eth adapter enx<mac> does NOT —
       0 inbound multicast; never use it). See docs/go2-drive-activation-design.md.

     HISTORY / correction: a prior conclusion (xml comment + commit 92b6158) was
     "single interface, NO lo, NO Peers", derived against the enx adapter — whose
     self-loopback happened to work, so same-host did not need lo there. That does
     NOT hold on eno1 (self-loopback broken). The earlier lo+enx failure (commit
     72dfabb, retcode -3) was caused by adding a unicast <Peer>, not by lo itself;
     this config has NO Peer. Modern <Interfaces> syntax (deprecated
     <NetworkInterfaceAddress> silently breaks binding).

     RESIDUAL UNKNOWN (hardware-gated): whether the Go2 WRITE path (us ->
     /api/sport/request) works under lo+eno1 is unverified — the Go2 was not
     connected when this was set. Validate with docs/jetson-nav-run-order.md gates:
     /sportmodestate READ, then matched-sub on /api/sport/request, before motion.
     If the Go2 is not discovered, try eno1-only TEMPORARILY to isolate (it will
     break same-host but proves external reach), then restore lo+eno1.

     name= the onboard NIC on the Go2 (192.168.123.x) subnet — default eno1. Verify
     with: ip a   (NICs/IPs can reshuffle per power-cycle). -->
<CycloneDDS>
  <Domain Id="any">
    <General>
      <Interfaces>
        <NetworkInterface name="eno1" priority="10" multicast="default" />
        <NetworkInterface name="lo" priority="1" multicast="default" />
      </Interfaces>
    </General>
  </Domain>
</CycloneDDS>
